XMLSpeaker - Class in org.hl7.xml.builder
An XMLSpeaker implements the SAX XMLReader interface but is meant to generate SAX events by means other than "reading" XML (e.g., by traversing some data structure.) The name comes from the similarity between reader and speaker: a reader is a speaker but a speaker speaks without necessarily reading.
